The paper focuses on learning-based approaches for robotic grasping using visual sensors, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) for object detection, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses fine-tuning the CNN using data from previous demonstrations, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves using a learning-from-demonstration approach, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves using a robotic manipulator, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
